      "full_name": "Public Joint Stock Company “Instrument Plant ‘Signal’”",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "PJSC “Instrument Plant ‘Signal’” is a Russian manufacturer of instruments and apparatus for measuring electrical quantities or ionizing radiation. Its products are provided to industrial enterprises and government institutions. The company’s products (including PKUZ-1A instrument complexes) are also used in military equipment, in order to detect gamma radiation and toxic substances. A technopark “Signal” was created by PJSC “Instrument Plant ‘Signal’” to boost industrial potential and is supported by the Russian Government. PJSC “Instrument Plant ‘Signal’” is therefore supporting materially Russia’s military and industrial complex and the Government of the Russian Federation, which is responsible for the annexation of Crimea and the destabilisation of Ukraine.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}